7. Resilience and Application-Level Self-Healing

The architecture distinguishes between Infrastructure Healing and Logical Healing.

Failure Scenario Analysis

Failure Scenario	System Response
Worker Process Hang	Orchestrator detects last_heartbeat timeout in task_runs; resets task to READY.
Node/Pod Death	Kubernetes restarts the pod; Kafka Partition Rebalancing triggers reassignment of uncommitted tasks.
Task Script Error	Worker emits task.failed; Orchestrator increments retry_count and applies backoff.

Retry Strategy

The system implements exponential backoff for failures. If a task fails, it is rescheduled with increasing delays. Only after the max_retries defined in task_definitions is exhausted is the task moved to the Dead Letter Queue (DLQ), triggering a terminal failure for the entire workflow run.


