8. Deployment Architecture and Elastic Scaling

The engine leverages the synergy between Kafka consumer lag and Kubernetes Horizontal Pod Autoscaling (HPA).

Mathematical Scaling Logic

The relationship between partitions and scaling is a hard constraint. Let P be the number of partitions in the task.ready topic and R be the number of Worker replicas. The system maintains: R \leq P Scaling R beyond P yields zero benefit, as the additional replicas will remain idle. Scaling is triggered when "Lag > Threshold," but is capped by P.

Graceful Shutdown

To maintain integrity during down-scaling, Workers must handle the SIGTERM signal. Upon receipt, the Worker stops polling Kafka, allows in-flight ProcessBuilder tasks to complete, commits final offsets, and then terminates.


